/* World War II */ I tried to verify the statement. I found that the population of ethnic Poles already exceeded the pre-war population in 1950 (Source: Kazimierz Piesowicz, Demograficzne skutki II wojny swiatowej, Studia Demograficzne, No. 1/87, 1987, pp. 103-136). Only if we consider all minorities in pre-war Poland (including Ukrainians, Belarusians, German-speaking Jews and Germans) the statement itself might be true. However, many of them did not die in the war, but were expelled later.
